{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"metadata":{"title":"centerOffset","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"property","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"title":"centerOffset","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapLibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","type":"topic","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","title":"MLNAnnotation","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"title":"MLNAnnotationView","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"}}}